Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Slice the @bell pepper{1}(sliced into strips) into strips.

Cut the @lime{1}(cut into wedges) into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, boil the @egg noodle nest{125%g}, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Next, add the pepper and @sugar snap peas{80%g} to the frying pan and fry, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @bulgogi sauce{100%g} and @soy sauce{25%ml} and fry, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles to the frying pan. Toss to coat and warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{splash} if it's dry.

Share the chicken noodles between your bowls.

Serve with a lime wedge on the side for squeezing over. Enjoy!